## Brute force Attack: using every combination there is to try to gain access to password.
- Brute force attack: try every combination starting with 0000 and so one, to gain access. Usually done in automated fashion
- Dictionary attack: using a list of words, phrases and password dumps to try to gain access. Also done automattically or done by some prompt to keep trying one-after-another.
- Credential Stuffing: grab credential dumps and will try every single possible combination in hopes to gain access.

How to defend:
- Longer passwords/phrases (a trick here is to use a password manager)
- Multifactor Authentication. you need something else other than password to login (recomend using an authiocator rather than SMS or email)
- Stay Vigilant

Common Tools used to perform this attack
- Hydra
- Hashcat
- John The Ripper
